We have implemented PaginatedTable component. The data is loading and the table + pagination is visible, but the loading spinner/overlay keeps rotating forever on top of the table (see attached screenshot). The page is usable, but the spinner never disappears.
Console warnings:

Multiple [Violation] 'setInterval' handler took 190-253ms
@supabase/gotrue-js: Lock "lock:sb-...-auth-token" was not released within 5000ms (React Strict Mode related)

Fix requirements:

In PaginatedTable.tsx (and every component that uses it):
Make sure isLoading state is properly toggled.
Use this exact pattern for fetching:tsxconst [data, setData] = useState([]);
const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(true);   // initial load = true
const [pageLoading, setPageLoading] = useState(false); // separate for page changes

const fetchData = async (page, filters) => {
  setPageLoading(true);
  try {
    const { data, count } = await supabase
      .from('games') // or whatever table
      .select('*', { count: 'exact' })
      .order('created_at', { ascending: false })
      .range((page-1)*pageSize, page*pageSize-1)
      // date filters...
      .then(res => res);
    setData(data || []);
    // update total count etc.
  } finally {
    setIsLoading(false);
    setPageLoading(false);
  }
};
Show spinner only when isLoading === true (initial load). For page changes use pageLoading or a small inline spinner.
Remove any overlay spinner that stays on after data arrives.

Fix performance warnings (setInterval):
The 5 live countdown timers are causing the violations.
Replace multiple setInterval with one single global timer (use a context or Zustand store) that updates all 5 sessions at once every 1000ms.
Or use requestAnimationFrame + timestamp check instead of setInterval.

Fix Supabase auth lock warning:
In the auth listener (useEffect with supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange), make sure you properly return the unsubscribe function.
Example:tsxuseEffect(() => {
  const { data: { subscription } } = supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange((event, session) => { ... });
  return () => subscription.unsubscribe();
}, []);
Temporarily comment out <React.StrictMode> in main.tsx to confirm it disappears in development.

Debug help:
Add console.log('PaginatedTable: isLoading changed to', isLoading); right after every setIsLoading.
Make sure the fetch function runs once on mount and after filter/page change.


Update all history pages that use PaginatedTable (Activity, Admin tables, Referral, etc.).
Do NOT change the pagination or date filter logic — just fix the stuck loading spinner.
Generate the updated PaginatedTable.tsx + any other changed files.
Start fixing now.

